shortDescription: A interactive visual novel exploring your relationship with the family.
longDescription: I experienced the transition during winter break in 2020. Family issues add up with the societal disaster, I realized, for the first time in my life, how much my family has contributed to make me live to the place of where I am. I also realized how much I am unable to be separated from them. Therefore, I want to use my senior project to record this significant mental tradition. I also wish to target teenagers and young adults. They are just those people around me or at my age, who I wish they can also feel or start to feel the same.

shortDescription: A cybernetic installation piece.
longDescription: This is an installation piece that critiques the cybernetic worldview, a paradigm that sees the entire world in terms of a system. It's a demonstration of what is lost in natural processes when one breaks down all phenomena into discrete, measurable parts in order to understand its whole. The piece is comprised of a fish tank with a shallow whirlpool that moves leaves in a circular motion. The shadows from those leaves are read by photo-resistors attached to the bottom of the tank, which is then transferred into a linear circuit via a conglomeration of wires and transistors. The final output is a “low res” image of the tank, with “approximations” of where the leaves are. The dynamic fluid flow makes the output seem random. The wires and circuitry are fully exposed, showing the whole system in its entirety.
usedSoftware: Made with analog circuits, aquatic motors, and a fish tank.

projectTitle: The Essential Guide to Accessible Techniques of Making a Clothing Brand
shortDescription: A zine series to help individuals interested in creating a clothing brand.
longDescription: The overarching theme of my senior project this year is about the accessibility to making how to go about making clothing brand that uses an array of lo-fi to hi-fi tools, lo-fi tools such as using acrylic paint and textile medium to paint on different articles of clothing such as jean jackets to doing hand embroidering designs using embroidery floss and embroidery linen. My project is about the means of giving potential clothing designers options and ways for them to design their products even if they don’t have access to facilities such as MakerSpaces, HackerSpaces and Seamstress shops.
usedSoftware: Adobe Illustrator, Adobe Photoshop, Adobe Indesign, Acrylic Paint, Embroidery Floss, Canvas, Linen

shortDescription: A satire game about media censorship
longDescription: Inspired by both Iceland PM steps aside after protests over Panama Papers revelations and media censorship in China, one of the functions of media is to hold government officials and institutions accountable for their actions; however, due to media censorship, such function is limited and the function as propaganda becomes dominant. It is hard for people who live under media censorship to judge the environment where they live in without bias. Thus, I created a satire game for people to experience media censorship in an imaginary town and to reflect the influence of media censorship. The game is based on Pokémon Essentials for fast prototyping purpose. The player is going to interact with town residents to uncover an illegal activity happening in Harmony Town.

shortDescription: A cardboard prototype of a communicative wearable that wraps around the user’s wrist.
longDescription: This wearable explores forms of communication via embodied technology. Like any medium, the wearable acts as an extension of the user. Through this, the device becomes a part of the user’s body in an attempt to embody aethereal data, the packets of information that are being transferred on a network. A flex sensor is attached to the user’s finger and a haptic motor can be placed anywhere the user chooses. The device comes in a pair. As the user flexes their finger, the haptic motor on their partners end vibrates and vice versa. With a photon microcontroller mounted on a soldered protoboard, the device utilizes Wi-Fi capabilities to communicate with one another through TCP connection.
usedSoftware: ​​​​​​​Made with Photon’s Particle microcontroller, haptic motors, and circuits.

projectTitle: New York City Guide: A Rats Perspective
shortDescription: four pamphlets, introducing the transportation, food, accommodation, and relationships in New York City through one of the rats’ six senses.
longDescription: The amount of rats in New York City is approximately 24% of the human population. In addition, the enormous quantity of trash in the city allows them to stay 150 ft within their birthplace and still have plenty of food resources. I am curious about a rats’ way of living. How do these rodents practice various grades of Commensalism living with humans? What does New York City look like, feels like, in the sense of a rat? I created four pamphlets, introducing the transportation, food, accommodation, and relationships in New York City through one of the rats’ six senses.

shortDescription: A friending website which people can make new friend and share their drawing.
longDescription: The goal of Atelier is to provide a way to eliminate the boundary between people thereby appreciating everyone’s differences, and the specific purpose of Atelier is to address issues concerning introverts and extroverts bias. Rethinking how to use technology and creations to awake people to know and respect the diversified personality traits, my solution is to use art making as a tool for friending.

shortDescription: A website that automatically generates the definition of "The Cloud"
longDescription: “Cloud 9” was inspired when I was going through my photos in 2013 on google cloud. We all know that the cloud is actually a server farm. But to me, it is also a mix of emotions and memories. So what exactly is "The Cloud" ? To give "The Cloud" a possible definition, I used an API  to pull a random image of the cloud from GIPHY every time the adjective& noun is replaced in the sentence. I named it Cloud 9 because my memories in the cloud are generally happy ones.

shortDescription: Interactive website
longDescription: $$$ is a interaction piece inspired by my grandpa. After he went to community college to learn how to use his smart phone, he has been sending pictures to me via Wechat. Many of his messages are filled with gods, flowers, dollar bills, wishing you a good fortune. I want to mimic the odd yet intriguing aesthetics.

shortDescription: A clock that represents the 5 stages of lost and grief.
longDescription: This color clock represents each emotion in “5 stages of grief”. The 5 stages are 01. Denial and Isolation 02.Anger 03 Bargaining 04.Depression 05.Acceptance. The colors are noted in my sketch and were chosen according to my intuition towards these sensations. These gradient colors will gradually change as time goes by. For example, the black in "Denial and Isolation" will gradually change into the red in "Anger". A complete cycle will take 60 minutes approximately, giving each stage 12 minutes. ( Sped up in documentation)

shortDescription: A series of graphic design for an animated film based on Italo Calvino's book The Complete Cosmicomics.
longDescription: This project is an expansion of one of my previous projects for Motion Graphics class where I had to design characters and styled animation frames for Italo Calvino's story, The Distance of the Moon. I was fascinated by Calvino's writing and decided to read more of his works. Upon finishing the entire book of The Complete Cosmicomics, I designed posters and teaser graphics that captured the feelings conveyed by the story.

shortDescription: Portrait commissions. All proceeds went to charity.
longDescription: At the beginning of this year, I decided to start doing portrait commission to raise money for charity. All portraits are pay-as-you-wish so everyone, regardless of their financial ability, can contribute something. Within the first 2 weeks, I was able to raise enough money to support 4 girls to attend school for an entire year. All the portraits I will be submitting are the people who contributed to this project!

shortDescription: A project that proves the six degrees of separation theory found in the Asian American community.
longDescription: This project came to be because I was always fascinated on how small this world is based on my personal experience. I think this project is something that hasn't been created before. I hope to drive conversation and awareness to this theory in a different cultural context.

otherNames: Junnan Lyu, Ellen Shiu, Jenny Huang
shortDescription: A daily newspaper that illustrates a future world centered around the philosophy and ethics of filial piety.
longDescription:
This project is a revision of the final project we worked on during Professor Ahmed Ansari's class, Design Other Worlds. Filial Piety(孝), as one of the fundamental ethics of achieving benevolence (仁), has been inherited as a traditional ethic that enhances the importance of family in Taiwan and other East Asian cultures. It is a key virtue of respect for one's parents, elders, and ancestors.

Our world is located in Taiwan, and the time is set to 2030. We selected five stories from The Twenty-four Filial Exemplars(二十四孝), a classic text of Confucian filial piety written during the Yuan dynasty (1260–1368). We alter and re-contextualize them with the further advance of technology with the essence of  Filial Piety, and named it as Filial Piety Futurism. Besides a variety of news, we also embed the philosophy and concept into an advertisement, weather forecast, and even public commendation. Through providing this alternative future world, we wish to reflect upon a series of issues that are very present in our current society.

shortDescription: The Metro ARchive is an immersive augmented reality experience that enables users to view historic city streets as they were centuries ago.
longDescription: The project was developed in collaboration with the New York Times Research and Development Lab for the NYC Media Lab Spatial Computing for News Challenge. It was created to experiment with how emerging media can revolutionize the way we document and share journalism. The app highlights forgotten urban history for users to see on-site or at home using AR. It is a proof of concept for what could eventually become a series of walkable experiences where entire city blocks are explorable in immersive AR.
usedSoftware: App: XCode, Swift, ARKit, SceneKit; Design: Illustrator, Sketchup, Maya, Photoshop, Blender

shortDescription: A customizable anti facial recognition helmet.
longDescription: How might we use critical design to call attention to hidden surveillance technologies that are violating our rights to privacy? It’s clear that we need a tool to be used in opposition to the emerging products using facial data as a weapon against us. We need protection. We need Antiface.
usedSoftware: Fusion 360 / 3D Printing (PLA & SLA) / Esp32 IDE ArtNet DMX512 / After Effects / Resolume

shortDescription: A visual collage series about the struggles of addiction.
longDescription: I have a lot of loved ones in my life who struggle with addiction, but I've never really known what that means to them or what they go through emotionally. I decided to do this series as a creative way to show what someone who struggles with addiction might experience. My target audience is people like myself who do not personally know what it means to be addicted to drugs, but who have loved ones who do. My goal is to take the data and numbers out of the equation and show pure emotions through photos and graphic techniques.
usedSoftware: Adobe Creative Suite/ Apple MacBook Pro/ Canon T5i digital camera

shortDescription: Raising funds for low-income households affected by the COVID-19 outbreak back home in the Philippines
longDescription:
The Philippines is on the brink of a humanitarian crisis. The enhanced community quarantine in Luzon has left informal "no work, no pay" workers (street vendors, public transportation drivers, etc.) and their families extremely vulnerable. This lockdown, which has been extended to last until April 31, 2020, has also made it nearly impossible for daily wage earners to stay afloat without any outside support.

A vast majority of these contractual workers and daily wage earners come from impoverished neighborhoods whose residents earn far below the required legal required daily minimum wage of PHP 537— the equivalent of only USD $10. Thus even the slightest disruption to their livelihoods has grave consequences.

For every USD $10 raised, Kapit will send a relief package to a low-income household affected by the COVID-19 outbreak in the Philippines.

shortDescription: A two-part digital and physical experience that promotes self-care and allows people to fall asleep on the New York subways without missing their stop.
longDescription: As a commentary on consumerism, I created a motion graphics advertisement promoting the most universally accessible and free self-service: naps. From there, I further pushed this message by designing and prototyping my own physical product, a silk sleeping mask with different subway stations printed onto it to inform bystanders of when to wake the user up for their stop. A simple yet effective solution to a commonly-experienced problem, this product both allows us to ease our way around the exploitative nature of the nine-to-five life, while still contributing to our capitalist society that put us in this position in the first place.
usedSoftware: Silk Masks, Laser Cutter, Adobe After Effects, Adobe Illustrator

shortDescription: Live-streamed interactive sound installation using data collected from plants.
longDescription: This project is an effort to grant sonic agency to plants. It inquires what music made by plants would sound like using sensors in the soil and on the plants themselves. This data is then processed in Max/MSP and mapped to oscillators so that we hear the movement of the plants.

shortDescription: Natural Artifice is a project that explores plant intelligence and intentionality through L-System generations.
longDescription: Natural Artifice is a Max/Jitter patch based on an L-System GUI developed by Robin Parmar. The patch contains an L-System Generator that interacts with a video asset from the 1978 Documentary, The Secret Life of Plants, in addition to a frequency generator that emits sine waves based on the position of the L-System’s location. It also includes a voiceover discussing plant intelligence and our perception of it.

shortDescription: Softwarpipes is a new musical interface that simulates the sound and gestures of a bagpipe.
longDescription: Using an Arduino and MaxMSP, Softwarpipes plays on the features of the bagpipes, a traditional Celtic instrument. It was created as part of a larger project that examined the political history of the bagpipes and placed it in modern times. The Arduino acts as the melody control (or 'chanter') while a phone sending XYZ rotation data to Max acts as the drone control.

shortDescription: Cyborg, Emotions, Control is a point-and-click narrative game where the protagonist experiences emotions outside of their bodily control due to an emotional modulator malfunction and the player, progressing day by day, gradually uncovers the story.
longDescription: In Cyborg, Emotions, Control, the player experiences the story from the perspective of a 23-year-old junior marketing analyst who has owned an emotional modulator since she was 10. However, the device malfunctioned and she started to experience, unprecedentedly, uncontrollable emotional ups and downs. The player gradually uncovers the story of the protagonist, including her lifestyle, relationship with her parents and relationship with her emotional modulator. In the end, the player needs to make a decision to give up the modulator or replace it with a new model. Do you choose agency over your own emotions with unknown consequences? Or do you wish to keep the perks of staying calm and blissful with the implant of a cybernetic device?

projectTitle: Bouncing head and an inverted head- two forks of a project
shortDescription: A bouncing ball which has your head as reflection. The ball can bounce off your head as you hit it- heading the ball experience created using ml5
longDescription:
The concept stems from a sculpture created by artist Lucy Humphrey at the Sculpture by the sea exhibition at Bondi. The sculpture is called Horizon. I remember this sculpture from a research I was doing for the ideation class last month. This is a sculpture model of a water filled ball she was presented during her visit in Venice.
 I have created a replica of the model which creates a pseudo reflective effect using the video feedback. The reflective ellipsoid replaces the face of the user and moves with the motion. The background is the live video feedback of the user and the ball inverts the feedback and moves according to the user’s motion. As with the library, it also detects multiple users and creates multiple reflective models. I have used ML5 Posenet and WebGL to mimic the effects of the model. This effect is also mimicked by a lot of photographers to incorporate an inverted image using the water filled ball.
Fork1:
While the actual sculpture is created using a water filled sphere to reflect the surroundings, I have mimicked the effect by rendering the camera as texture on a 3D model which adjusts itself according to the face dimensions and co-ordinates.


Fork 2:
I have also created a bouncing sphere which bounces off the head as a fork for the same. I did not want to incorporate it as it contrasts with the concept. The bouncing ball responds to gravity and the position of the head.  This is a result of a teeny bit of curiosity which stemmed while exploring animation of objects independent but at the same time dependent of the user’s animation.

shortDescription: In certain mythologies, it is said that once a person dies, the soul leaves the body leaving the body to dust back into earth and blend into it. This installation project mimics this idea.
longDescription: In this improvised project, the user gets to wait for his/her soul to depart from the body. The body will remain in the screen while the soul will move with the user’s movement (Pixel transformations). Once the user moves out of the screen’s/camera’s view, his/her body turns to dust(ML5)

shortDescription: I have created an automatic novel generator which makes it look like the computer is generating a novel by itself.
longDescription:
I have made use of my two favourite books- Anne of Green Gables and Alice in Wonderland.
Anne is a character who has immense imagination and Alice in Wonderland is a book entirely dependent on imagination. The project focuses on combining these elements to extend Anne’s imagination, coz what more imagination can Anne have than the imaginative world of Alice?
Each page is saved once completed so that it can be collected for printing.

shortDescription: A Virtual Reality Wildlife Photography Simulator
longDescription: Snap Odyssey is a virtual reality wildlife photography simulator. Take pictures of animals in virtual reality with your virtual camera and learn more about them. Highly inspired from photography-based games like Pokemon Snap, Fatal Frame, and Beyond Good & Evil. It was a personal project turned into a class project and then an actual project which will be collaborating with the American Museum of Natural History this year. I made this because I love animals since I was young, the game features recently endangered animals which allows players aware of their current problems and understand more about them.
usedSoftware: Unity, Blender, Google Poly, Oculus Quest

shortDescription: ‘Where Are You From?’ is an interactive augmented reality experience surrounding the second generation immigrant community in American suburbs.
longDescription: Where Are You From? is an Augmented Reality experience surrounding the second generation immigrant community raised in the American suburbs.  The main character is allowed to enter your own home in order to draw parallels to shared experiences and tell its story.  The experience represents the notion of the blended American: an individual with multicultural roots uniquely positioned to advance American society towards a more inclusive state.  I envision a future for this experience in suburban classrooms as an introduction to cultural studies explorations within their own communities.
usedSoftware: Metaverse Studio, Adobe Illustrator, Premier, and AfterEffects

shortDescription: A VR music interface
longDescription: an immersive virtual reality experience with new musical interfaces called “VR Jam'', for people who want to create music or VR fans who know little about creating music, to make music from within a VR environment. The experience also comes with lessons to help users learn the basics of music making.

shortDescription: A photographic series exploring the boundaries of human visual perception and color.
longDescription: "Duality" is a series of six digitally manipulated photographs aimed at exploring the intricacies of human visual perception. In perceptual psychology, how we perceive visual stimuli can be explained by the flow of information towards the visual cortex, which is split into the left and right hemispheres of our brain. Interestingly, if different images are projected into each eye at the same time, our mind will "switch" back and forth between the two photographs, generating a phenomenon known as "binocular rivalry". The images of "Duality" have been altered to generate this specific visual effect, and viewers who observe the images through 3D glasses can experience this surreal scene through their own eyes. (Due to coronavirus however, viewers who are unable to obtain 3D glasses will have to use their iPhone color tint feature to view the images).

shortDescription: mobile accessible interface and experience for Netflix Party feature.
longDescription:
Netflix Party allows users to watch videos and chat with their friends together simultaneously. Although, the feature is only accessible as a Chrome extension through the desktop browser. During this Covid-19 pandemic, where everyone is urged to practice social distancing and be quarantined, the feature is very conventional, since most people who have a desktop are at home.

However, Netflix Party is a distinct and innovating feature specific to Netflix. Therefore,  I hope that it will continue to be relevant, despite changing circumstances that is why I believe a personal devices iteration would continue to push an innovative and futurist vision.

shortDescription: A VR experience based on a generation‘s memory
longDescription: This is my thesis project and it's about a generations' memory。

shortDescription: Staying connected in the time of isolation
longDescription: The project aims to facilitate in-depth conversation with trusted friends for those who are experiencing distress and low mood. Research has shown speaking about your experiences and emotions are helpful to overcome low mood by forming narrative identity and feeling supported. However, many people who wish to talk about their experiences and emotions don't always know how to initiate the conversation. In this time of isolation, building that empathetic connection is more important than ever.

shortDescription: In this uncertain time, Squish uses their imagination to have fun and goes on an adventure with what’s around the house.
longDescription: In my photography class, our first project coincided with the switch to online classes and the placement of social distancing measures. Squish is my little stress-reliving squishie and always brought me a sense of calm and positivity. Because Squish is very small, I had set out to capture what the world looks like in Squish’s eyes. How everyday items, big or small, with a bit of imagination and creativity, can create whole new worlds for Squish. Through this collection of images, I hope to convey bring a sense of joy and uplifting spirit during this period of uncertainty.

shortDescription: A tool for poster makers to create static or dynamic posters in a minute with surprise.
longDescription: This is a tool for poster makers to create static or dynamic posters in a minute with surprise. The learning cost of traditional design software is too high for normal users without a design background. However, generative design is a powerful method that can be applied in poster design to accelerate your design process and make a surprise. Besides, it will be easier to create dynamic posters with this tool than others just by moving your finger.

shortDescription: A digital magazine featuring interviews with NYU artists
longDescription: This magazine serves the purpose of highlighting artists at NYU, their work, their motivations, and how they are dealing with challenges today especially with the global pandemic of COVID-19. It was created in the hopes of showing the NYU community what students here have to offer, and provide a platform for the artists.

shortDescription: Ritka is a magazine by women, about women, for women.
longDescription: The project titled Ritka, is a magazine that showcases the stories of diverse women in a real and raw manner in an effort to initiate genuine conversations about expectations, ambitions, obstacles, and over-comings. Every woman in my life as well as their strength and endurance has inspired the creation of this project. This magazine was made to tell and highlight stories that otherwise may have gone unheard to inspire any female identifying reader looking for relatability and connection. The goal is to launch discussions that are typically not found in traditional women’s magazines and to uncover the complexity of people and their diverse lives.

shortDescription: Bumi is a niche seasonal eatery–delivered to your home using sustainable ingredients and process.
longDescription: Bumi is a service design intervention with goals to provide a platform to home cooks, to promote niche-ethnic culture and community through food and integrating it with a sustainable delivery service. We specialize in niche cuisines by rotating the themes every few months (e.g. This month's theme is Javanese, next one is Chifa (Peruvian). By partnering with home cooks, we are able to bring you the most authentic dining experience whilst also keeping our process as sustainable as possible by using reusable containers and using local and seasonal ingredients whenever possible.
usedSoftware: AfterEffects, Photoshop, Illustrator, PremierePro, Stainless Steel, Biodegradable Packagings, Recyclable Packagings, Glass

shortDescription: Data Visualize the emotions about the news topic.
longDescription: I always wondering about the relationship between readers and news articles online, and the circle of news production. How's the information transit from news to user, and becoming other resources for another news article. The work will mainly use Web Scraper and API to collecting the general emotion data from News Articles, Twitter, then visualize the data from those Data.

shortDescription: A Playful IoT Domestic Device that Facilitates and Enhances Long-Distance Communication
longDescription:
Advanced technology in public transportation has made travel easier than ever before, and the emerging digital media is connecting everyone 24/7 regardless of the physical distance and time difference.

However, the "always connected" illusion created by the "always available" media tech seems to make us harder to find the right time to actually connect with our loved ones, specially family members who are living apart.

"I thought you are online so I sent you a message, but soon then I realized you are sleeping at this time." Leaving asynchronous messages has gradually become the new norms nowadays, while being different from the old-fashioned letter because of those messages tend to be trivial with probably less intentionality.

hOOOme is a playful IoT lighting display product that allows people to update and share online availability status with different colors. Users can customize the color coded system for more playful experience. This design aim to increase the intentionality during long-distance communication with a fun and ritual-like interaction.
usedSoftware: Arduino IDE, NodeMCU, Blynk Cloud Service, LED lights, Cardboard, Wires, Ping-pong balls

shortDescription: Doughland is an imaginative adventurous land where player can learn about the bread dough fermentation by playing the role of a yeast.
longDescription:
VR is a compelling media technology that allows immersive storytelling from 1st person perspectives, and it is also a powerful tool for people to explore a mundane object from a micro level, from the inside of it, by making an imaginative world with virtual reality.

Bread fermentation is a beautiful bio-chemical process which happens inside a dough, and I think it will be helpful to educate this process by allowing us "getting into the bread".

In this VR game, player can travel freely and interact with the objects and learn about the ingredients and facts about yeasts with a poetic narration, while on his/her way to "escape the bread dough".

It's designed for younger players with parental assist, and a potential application location will be museum or exhibition.
usedSoftware: Unity3D, Oculus Rift, Blender, SteamVR, Illustrator

projectTitle: THE GIRL STUCK IN THE BUBBLE
shortDescription: An interactive narrative game about a love story between people who are not good at expressing their emotions or needs
longDescription:
There is a large group of people in China who are not good at expressing their emotions or needs proactively, and they are troubled by this issue. They tend to put the needs of others first and habitually ignores or suppresses his or her own needs.
I want to design an interactive narrative game about a love story between two people who are not good at actively expressing their emotions and needs. The game allows players to see the positive and negative effects of being too "thoughtful" in intimate relationships, allowing players to understand the importance of communication and building empathy.

shortDescription: Bluefoot! is a documentary acting as a time capsule of quarantine, of my work and life the past four years, and a critique of the COVID-19 Response.
longDescription: My original idea for a narrative film with multiple protagonists confronting absurd situations was cancelled because we all found ourselves confronting the absurd situation that is COVID-19. Filmmaking is the medium I enjoy working in the most, so I felt I would continue to work with it, but from a nonfiction, raw perspective. I'd been wanting to do a reflective work for a long time now and saw this as an opportunity to pivot and leave behind a time capsule for my future self and for people who may forget the consequences and insanity of this current time period. The film is divided into several chapters comprised of music, commentary, home footage, archived footage, and found footage from online, it is both personal, humorous, and unique in its nonlinear, abstract approach.
usedSoftware: Sony A6400 Camera, Sennheiser Microphone, Adobe Premier.

submissionType: I'm submitting a collection of Fashion Engineering Projects
shortDescription: A multidisciplinary approach to creation – highly sophisticated, integrated, and advanced functional materials engaging with inclusive design and adaptive wear.
longDescription: My mind sees science and fashion as two areas that were born to intertwine. Uniting the contrasting uniqueness of science and fashion we can adapt others’ perceptions of themselves and create strong messages through the power of creation and innovation.I want to explore the fabrication and technicalities of the clothing of the future incorporating 3D printing, CAD, biosensing, networked devices, and laser cutting in a sustainable way. My goal is to make people feel good – by wearing something unique and never seen before, one will feel empowered and people will look at you like they have never before. By merging my two passions I strongly believe that it is possible to develop products while being true to an identity that represents avant-garde structured looks using sustainable process and socially responsible manufacturing to let the most diverse group of people express themselves through exclusive ways that will cause an impact on others just as the release of a new ground-breaking research discovery.
usedSoftware: Sewing Machine, Sticky Notes, Failed 3D prints, 3D printer, Hot Glue Gun, Irridescent Fabric, Tulle, Autodesk Maya, Photoshop, Illustrator, Laser Cutter, Gold Leaves, Vinyl.

shortDescription: “In Theory” is a series of zines aimed at educating college students on mental health.
longDescription: Mental illnesses are more common than people think and mental health is important for an individual's well being. My idea behind this project is that, in theory, if more people are aware of mental health and why it’s important, more people will be open to seeking treatment when needed. Despite the stigma around mental health, there are many other barriers to treatment that need to be addressed; thus, this series of zines attempts to bring some of those barriers to light. Some of the topics covered include an introduction to mental health and why it's important.

shortDescription: A photo series.
longDescription: A series showcasing New Chinatown and Old Chinatown (post gentrification and current gentrification). I captured the people in the neighborhood, the buildings and posters to showcase the gentrified and original LES.
usedSoftware: Back board, camera, flowers, dispolable cameras

shortDescription: An Egg, A Baby, A Chicken
longDescription: I got inspired by the scene when Randall tries to use the scream extractor on Boo from Monster Inc., and I always want to create an animation showing the surrealistic interaction between human beings and stuff animals. Every life, or object, born with a meaningful reason at a critical moment, and our consciousness is connected. This animation is created with MAYA and rendered with Arnold. A fun fact is that in order to make the baby fully act out the scene in my mind, I motion captured myself with motive and applied those data to the baby I rigged.

projectTitle: Mindful Digital - Reducing Screen time through Ubiquitous Computing
shortDescription: Mindful Digital is a smart “dumb bag” that promotes a mindful use of digital devices and encourages you to develop better habits.
longDescription: The project aims to design an intervention to reduce the screen time of the user through ubiquitous computing and help develop better habits. The system is designed to provide feedback through three mediums – visual, auditory and haptic. The ubiquitous computing approach is used to design the intervention, so that it seamlessly blends into the user’s daily routine.

shortDescription: The purpose of this project is to start discussions about universal design and the importance of access for people in the disability community.
longDescription:
Persons with disabilities face widespread lack of accessibility to current built environments such as roads, housing, public buildings, and spaces. This project focuses on the experiences of wheelchair users and aims to bring awareness to the microaggressions and lack of accessibility of the urban living experience.

To help bring awareness an interactive narrative was developed to help educate the next generation of students to think about universal design and accessibility. With this game, I hope to educate people on the microaggressions of the urban experience for Millenials and Gen Z that live in urban areas.

Read Dissertation here: https://www.yumpu.com/en/document/read/63334257/universal-access-ny
usedSoftware: Javascript, Webflow, HTML & CSS, Adobe Illustrator, Adobe Photoshop, Adobe XD, Visual Code Studio, Github

shortDescription: Bass Hug is a cushion device that vibrates to the bass sound of the music you are listening to and allows you to feel the music by holding it.
longDescription: Bass Hug is a cushion device that vibrates to the bass sound of the music you are listening to and allows you to feel the music by holding it. I wanted to create a device that would enhance the experience of listening to music at home. This device was inspired in a situation where I was unable to go to a live concert due to the impact of the COVID-19. The device uses Raspberry Pi with Python programming to analyze the frequency of the music and control the vibration of eight vibrating motors in response to the bass. This device is primarily for meditation use by focusing on music and vibration, but it may also be used for any application that enhances the musical experience.

shortDescription: Mobile Application designed to aid in choosing a restaurant for you and your friends.
longDescription: When trying to pick a restaurant with a large group of friends, it is often very difficult to come to any decision between indecisiveness and disagreements. We asked how might we aid this process by making the decision process easy and pain-free. We worked on creating a react native application with a fun and intuitive UI. The app is targeted towards young people between the ages of 16 and 35 who live or travel to cities often. It is intended to be used on the spot; you and your friends are looking for food nearby and need help with picking what type of food and the restaurant so one person pulls out their phone to use our App. They take the quiz with the friends and are given a restaurant to go to.
usedSoftware: React Native, Expo, Figma and Illustrator

shortDescription: An experiment in creating an alternative visual topography for the city
longDescription: This project is the first phase in a bigger experiment for creating an experiential mediated urban walk that allows people to explore the hidden dimension of their built environment which is the data and the information that annotate this environment. This phase allows people to view existing urban annotations and then annotate on their own by uploading their own images, texts, and sounds to add personalized attributes to the city they dwell in. The final project will be using mobile augmented reality as a tool that enables the revealing process, which is navigating a city of virtual data, not only brick and mortar.

shortDescription: Dying For Your Entertainment is an interactive experience commenting on the growing interest in true crime documentaries.
longDescription: Dying For Your Entertainment is based on the growing interest in true crime documentaries and podcasts over the past few years. This experience comments on how victims have no control over what is said or is not said about them in these shows and usually focuses on the killer's story. The main goal of this project is to bring awareness to people who are listening and watching that these victims were murdered, and these companies are using it as a form of profit and entertainment.
usedSoftware: sketch, invision, proto.io, after effects, illustrator

shortDescription: The Launch of onthis's Musical Career for 2020.
longDescription:
A collection of music that will distributed over time after this semester is over. The moment one of the song is exceptionally well against the others that have come before it, the EP will drop the month after that. I made this to prove to myself that I CAN create a great collection of music in a very short period of time. I got inspired from a Steve Jobs's commencement speech that indicated to those who were listening, "Did you do everything that you could today? And are you happy with what you've done? If you die tomorrow, did you accomplish all that you wanted to accomplish?" I wanted to prove to others that my music is a force to be reckoned with in the Christian Music Industry and the Music Industry as a whole to be honest. It's a collection of work that will be distributed over time and also released as an ENTIRE body of work in the future, it can be listened to and watched (with visualizers and music videos) on all streaming platforms and on YouTube. It's for whoever wants to listen to a new voice that isn't afraid of being vulnerable and letting out all of their feelings on beautiful compositional soundscapes.

- onthis.
"your best friend"
usedSoftware: Pro Tools, Guitars, Vocals, Bass Guitar, Rokit 5 Monitors, ATH-M50x Headphones, and lots of Water.

shortDescription: This website is for human beans who are precious and beautiful but who struggle to see themselves that way.
longDescription: I made this because I often struggle with loving myself and I doubt myself every single day a lot more than I should. I find myself constantly apologizing for myself even if it's not my fault or if it's not a big deal. I wonder if I low-key think of myself as a burden. Especially in today's world where we are all constantly hustling, being sleep deprived, not taking care of  ourselves and feeling like we are not enough, I think my website is an important reminder that we are enough and that we deserve some self-care. Although encouragement from others helps, in the end it's up to you to love yourself. Because you are beautiful, you are enough. This website was made entirely out of HTML, CSS and little bit of Javascript. There are projects and bucket lists for people to explore and do that contribute to self-care. There are also sections for self-love messages and wholesome affirmations (That do not work on the back end however).
usedSoftware: I used HTML, CSS and Javascript.
instagram: No I do not :(((  However, now that you mention it, I think that would be a fun idea!

shortDescription: The Sensory Resources Guide For Museums will help museums implement accessibility resources to combat overstimulating environments to make them more widely accessible to all visitors.
longDescription: Sensory Resources Guide For Museums is a project that grew out of the Museum Accessibility class in Spring 2020. This graduate level course provided an opportunity for students to explore and develop prototypes as solutions to some of the accessibility challenges in museums. Our team was tasked with building solutions for Over-and-Under Stimulating Environments and learned that museums want to implement accessibility resources but often are unable to do so due to various constraints (budget, resources, bandwidth, etc). Our hope is that the Sensory Resource Guide is standardized, easy to use for museums staff, but more importantly, will help individuals with sensory processing challenges navigate different environmental settings. The suggested resources will provide visitors with the knowledge of what to expect when planning visits to museums and historic sites to optimize their experiences. Through our guide, we aim to increase museum engagement and interaction for visitors with different sensory needs. This class is a collaboration between the NYU Ability Project and the Intrepid Air, Sea and Space museum and this is funded through an IMLS grant (https://www.nyu.edu/about/news-publications/news/2019/october/nyu-ability-project-and-intrepid-.html).

shortDescription: The Figmental World of a Sketchbook is a graphic novel following the story of a Father and Daughter who are whisked away into the Daughter’s imaginary world and must find a way home.
longDescription: This project is a beginning means to reach towards my dreams. I want to tell the story inspired by my own experience of growing up  following themes of family, trust, and youth. A coming-of-age story that is geared towards people who are still discovering new things about themselves and the world, typically young adults. All this done in a visual storytelling medium that's memorable and immersive.
usedSoftware: Paint Tool Sai, Photoshop, InDesign, Paper, Pencil

shortDescription: A blog for college students to be motivated to live a healthy lifestyle!
longDescription: The project is intended to provide college students the motivation and ideas that we shared with each other throughout our four years at NYU. We wanted to create a blog because we are both visual people. This will allow us to express ourselves and show whatever projects we create.

shortDescription: Its a project that try to tackle the similarities between addictions of the minds, substance and more.
longDescription: Addiction is when a person is addicted to a substance or activity, which can lead to negative consequences. This idea inspires me to make a video game explaining how someone could get addicted. While everyone experiences events differently, there are similarities between people's addictions and the process of becoming addicted. I have had family and friends who were affected by addiction which is my biggest motivation in making this game.

shortDescription: A digital portfolio that will showcase a body of both ux and non-ux related works.
longDescription: I wanted to do this project because I knew that I needed to revamp my professional deliverables (resume, portfolio, cover letter, etc.) I wanted to specifically iterate my portfolio and push it into a space that felt more professional and polished than the one I was previously applying with. I want it to be oriented around the career path that I want to embark on (Interaction Design) and to showcase that through several detailed projects that I have worked on. This iteration that I am submitting for this showcase will be an emphasis on visuals and establishing a clear cut brand for myself as a designer and professional that will act as the fundamental style guide that will frame my website as I start to build out the projects that will be on the site this summer.
usedSoftware: Squarespace, Photoshop, Illustrator, XD, Mac Computer, iPad

shortDescription: this piece of composition is an experimentation of combining storytelling(spoken words) and musical sounds.
longDescription: this piece is part of my master thesis, a continuation of investigating the relationship between physical bodies and their sounds. one experienced by sight and touch and the other by ear, they point to the same vantage point where the truth lies - they are two distinct signs of the same knowledge, two drawers of the same cabinet. we cannot penetrate the cabinet, but we use the drawers as our only devices, to validate the existence of knowledge. I tell a fictional story of my interaction with this drawer cabinet, while interweaving sounds of virtual and real physical bodies.
usedSoftware: max msp, a physical modeling plugin i made

shortDescription: This project is a two-part installation juxtaposing the intimacy of physical space of my apartment, and the digital space of my laptop browser.
longDescription: (dis)comfort is created to imagine ideas of intimacy, familiarity and discomfort in quarantine - and how these interactions arise (or do not). In physical-space, "intimate" and comforting digital interaction are projection-mapped onto my bed: a video-chat with my boyfriend and other private/direct text messages. In digital-space, familiar, yet inconvenient interactions are embedded into my browser: my mother being able to send me one-way messages to clean my room, abrupt interruptions to my digital space and workflow from loved ones.

shortDescription: Falling Through Time is a short 3D animation representing the descent of losing identity and reality through time.
longDescription: "Falling Through Time" portrays an individual with an unknown identity falling through time and space, reaching out to old memories that represented who the individual once was. I made this to represent the looping descent into the unknown of life while time quickly passes by. Time passes all of us by faster as we grow older and often we try to latch onto parts of ourselves from childhood or our adolescent years as young adults. We go through life sometimes not fully aware of who we are or what we identify as trying to figure it out along the way. This piece was made with motion capture as well as traditional 3D animation.

shortDescription: A web app that connects your faraway families in a playful way
longDescription: In the context of a virus disease global outbreak, this project aimed to create a digital place where the families separated in distance can do shared activities, interact with each other and enjoy straight-up fun, focusing especially on the web-based video communication technology and interaction experience.

shortDescription: A platform to guide and connect prospective graduate students.
longDescription:
Connect-U is a platform that facilitates prospective graduate students with resources, guides, overall applying procedure and mentor ship for the process and major they want to pursue their graduate degree in. Connect-U is more of an information and peer help platform that enables prospective graduate students to connect with current graduate students/ alumni and help with their choice of major.

This project was built to close the gap of misinformation within students while also providing honest feedback and mentor ship. The hope is that by giving students a platform to honestly give their opinions and experiences, students would get the help they need directly from other students who were at some point in the same position as them.

After understanding the pressure points of the user and the journey, I thought the platform would need the following features.

Mentor Chat
Chat with alumni/ current students. This feature is the one that helps overcome the most important pressure point of the user- their confusion. Talking to someone who can become a mentor will not only facilitate prospective students to gain more knowledge about programs and universities but also have some to talk to about all their doubts and questions.

Resources
One more insight I gained from interviewing prospective students was the lack of resources available at one click. One has to really search deep and extensively on Google about great rankings and forums that help with the application process and help connect with students who are in the same process.

How to Guide
The How To Guide will act like a pre-checklist for all the students to start their application for Graduate School. I compiled a 10 easy step guide to apply to graduate school by looking at my graduate application notes from 2017 and major school requirements.

shortDescription: A love story between two fan's love for anime and for each other.
longDescription: A person's fandom is an extension of one's identity. Many people sometimes scared to share that aspects of themselves, because they fear of being judged my others. Storytelling is the best format to implement empathy from the fans’ point and view and animation has the room for creativity.The message of this animation short for both fans and non-fans is to show how fandom is not something to be shameful as it is part of one’s identity.

shortDescription: An AR experience that will make young adults more involved in politics by introducing them to the political candidates of the 2020 Election.
longDescription: This project was created to help younger adults and new voters become more educated on political candidates. I think that it is really important for younger voters to actually vote because this election will be really important for our future. A lot of young adults don’t want to take the time to watch 2 hr long debates or listen to podcasts about each candidate. This AR experience will provide a fun and immersive way for them to learn about the candidates and to see which candidates align with their own views.
usedSoftware: Adobe Illustrator, Photoshop, Autodesk Maya, and Spark AR

submissionType: A video walkthrough of a VR Visual Novel
shortDescription: ◯ is a VR visual novel discussing about the concept of individuality .
longDescription: ◯ is a VR visual novel discussing about the concept of individuality . What does it means to have individuality if your appearance does not represent yourself? How does a civilization look like with if they can communicate through pictures? As we are uploading and digitalizing our lives, let’s take a look at this future civilization.

projectTitle: Virtual Reality for Architects Learning Accessibility
shortDescription: Helping young architects learning accessibility through wheelchair experience in virtual reality
longDescription: The traditional way of reading and learning the ADA architecture design standards manual is inefficient and time-consuming, and it is even harder when it comes to putting the rules into an application. It is mainly because most architects don't have any experience of using accessible devices like a wheelchair, which helps them establish an actual and correct feeling and judgment of whether the space is appropriate for wheelchair users before construction. To increase architects’ awareness of ADA-compliant spaces and provide access to resources of learning standards of ADA accessibility architecture design, a virtual reality learning platform that is informative and easily accessible was created. Architects and users who want to learn accessibility gained an understanding of the importance of architecture accessibility design. And architects ultimately acknowledged a new perspective on how to use the specific architecture ADA standards in their daily design process.

shortDescription: A online exhibition that repackages sexist European high-art into feminist act.
longDescription: The inspiration of this project comes from my thesis research on marketplace feminist lingerie ads. The concept of feminism is exploited as a mere marketing strategy as the lingerie ads are deepening the objectification of female bodies, as it is a result of historical sexism. On the other hand, there are a lot of masterpieces in European high-art are based on female objectification imagery. Thus, I want to make a project on repackaging sexist European art into a feminist act with market place feminism strategy to show how the trendy feminist lingerie advertisement is merely "feminist because we say it is."

projectTitle: Virtual Reality Design Experience base on The Rider-Waite Tarot Deck
shortDescription: Virtual Reality Design Experience base on The Rider-Waite Tarot Deck
longDescription: The design combines the ancient divination art with VR technology to use immersive experiences to explain the meaning of each Major Arcana better.

projectTitle: Overbrimed: Web Based Experience for Conducting Sustainable Consumer Behavior in Fashion Industry
shortDescription: Overbrimed is web based experience aims to improve people’s awareness of the fashion industry environmental impact.
longDescription: What is laying behind the surface is the prevalence of consumerism, as well as people’s lack awareness towards the industrial situation: how much does presumptuous consumerism impact us environmentally and emotionally? Overbrimed is web based experience aims to improve people’s awareness of the fashion industry environmental impact. It walks users through the industrial production process, presents industrial consuming data, in order to guide consumers to lead a healthier way of shopping clothes.

shortDescription: An instrumental album presented on the Swunk Earth website.
longDescription: I am creating the Swunk Earth website as a container for a collection of 10 instrumentals I made. I made these instrumentals with the intention of invoking feelings of childhood nostalgia, outer space and the forest. These instrumentals are meant to showcase my skill-set and my unique sound that I have worked on developing over the past 9 years.
usedSoftware: Logic Pro X & WIX website builder

shortDescription: This is a Pop, Hip-Hop, and R&B fusion album (and short animation) that explores the mind of an insecure young man trying to find himself.
longDescription: Music has always been an important part of my life. I spent most of middle and high school playing violin in the school orchestra, and I even taught myself how to play piano and guitar. Funny enough, the only instrument I chose to highlight in this album is my voice. This album explores by favorite genres of music while giving me a platform to share my deepest insecurities and struggles. Enjoy!
usedSoftware: FL Studio, Autodesk Maya, Adobe Premiere Pro, Adobe Lightroom, Canva

shortDescription: An Online Interactive Exhibition about Coming Out
longDescription: Taken place on the free social VR platform Mozilla Hubs, “Closet” is an online interactive exhibition/performance about a Chinese queer's coming out story. Walking inside Jude's secret "closet" filled with childhood photos, love notes, and video interviews, the audience is introduced to Jude’s personal journey of learning about her sexuality and experience of coming out. With the live chat, emoji, and sharing functions in Mozilla Hubs, audiences are also encouraged to share their own stories.
usedSoftware: Adobe Dimension, Blender, Final Cut, Photoshop, etc.
instagram: No I don't. But I would love to promote my official instagram handle @judexsyd

shortDescription: In the distant future, humanity has begun to venture into space, and we need an app to record the planets we find.
longDescription: My project is a UI prototype planet guide for a future where humans are travelling through space. I made this because I wanted to design with bright, neon colors, and try a more speculative concept. In universe, this would be a way for laypeople who do not know about space to become more familiar with the planets being found, and how it affects their lives. In real life, this is for people who like speculative design, or design in general.

shortDescription: A resource to assist web developers in coding accessible websites.
longDescription: While navigating the internet, users with disabilities constantly encounter inappropriate alternative text, low contrast, empty links, and many other problems that keep them from navigating the web smoothly. How might we make accessible web design more intuitive for designers? More often than not, accessibility is an afterthought in web development. The problem with this after-the-fact implementation is that it is a complicated task which often results in bugs, stress, and inefficient code. My goal is to create a website that can function as a resource for developers to code accessible websites, hopefully making this process more intuitive for them. Using React.js, HTML, and CSS, I coded a website with resources such as code snippets, best practices, and accessible color palettes that developers can use to make their websites more accessible from the beginning of the design process.

projectTitle: Magic Bottle VR: Immersive Multimedia Game in Eye-Tracking in Virtual Reality and Multimodal Biometric Systems
shortDescription: An Interactive Virtual Reality (VR) game where the player will attempt to take out targets using magic objects in a given time. This game is utilizing biometric sensors and gaze-assisted VR headset.
longDescription: With the rising popularity of fitness wearables, virtual reality (VR) technologies, and biometric sensor technology continues to improve and expand into new form factors and use cases. One such area that we should expect to see in the very near future is biometrics in virtual reality (VR). VR gaming platforms have already begun to introduce basic data like heart rate in games and enterprise applications, signaling greater attention to biometric sensors in the VR development community. The synergy between biometrics and VR is accelerating as VR systems become more affordable and are adopted for diverse uses in healthcare, education, and business. Which targets multitude of audiences and impact multimedia platform to the next level. In this project, I will be creating an engine or unity plugin to generate a Virtual Reality (VR) based framework where researchers and designers can test their games using real-time biometric and eye-tracking sensors and its physiological data. I will be also showcasing a virtual reality game that uses this framework in a video platform and website.

shortDescription: Chroma is a website providing visual and audio content that uses color therapy to bring relief to people's everyday lives.
longDescription: Chroma was inspired by a document called 996 ICU where office workers documented their 9am - 9pm, 6 days a week schedules. Using the knowledge behind color therapy I was inspired to create an opportunity for office workers to find relief and retreat in my animations and audio guides that help facilitate meditation exercises. With an original idea to become a physical installation/booth, I have transitioned to a website platform during our current circumstances where you can explore all the different elements that I have created!
usedSoftware: Adobe Illustrator, AfterEffects, Premiere Pro, Photoshop, Weebly

shortDescription: collaborative zine centered around a specific topic, made to help promote artists.
longDescription: I am starting a collaborative zine as a means to help promote artists. I love making art, but  what means more to me in art, is seeing how others interpret the same idea. Starting a monthly/bi-monthly, publication where I can explore ideas with other creatives, as well has helping promote those creators, is something I find to be really invigorating.

shortDescription: womxn-led projects in music and tech
longDescription:
Vocal Friend allows you to control all the voices MacOS has to offer. You can speak and sing  with the voices of friends like Fred, who's always clear, albeit a bit robotic, or Bubbles, who does their best to communicate while underneath water.

Each voice has their own rasp, accent, and expressiveness. Vocal Friend gives you the ability to experiment with each voice, and decide what should be said through text and speech recognition and record the output.

A collective that collaborates on womxn-led music and tech projects.

projectTitle: Spring morning in the Han Palace
shortDescription: recreating traditional Chinese painting
longDescription: I personally like Chinese traditional art and notice that not many people interested in it as modernization take place in these few decades. Thus, I hope this project, from a relaxing and interesting aspect, attracts more people to understand and appreciate Chinese traditional painting. It is a recreation of the old painting, using the AR technique to reveal the hidden messages underneath.

shortDescription: I've designed a computer program that enables guitarists to play microtonal music on a standard guitar.
longDescription: I've created a program in Max that allows you to play microtonal music on a standard guitar. It recognises the pitch of a note that you are playing on the guitar and shift it if necessary to get a microtonal effect. It can also be used to fix intonation issues, similar to the curved true temperament frets. My project is about using technology to extend the possibilities of guitar.
usedSoftware: My guitar, the software program Max, a quarter inch to USB cable

shortDescription: An narrative-based game exploring how economic mobility is impacted by identity and social inequity.
longDescription: This project aims to educate players on the ways that economic mobility is influenced by race and identity within the context of the United States using the game, Life Like Mine. Life Like Mine employs a narrative-based approach to contextualize how racial stereotypes, inadvertent racism, systemic oppression sets up black youth for failure. Through playing the game, players will learn how the consequences of their choices are ultimately tied to identity and how the main character, a young black child, is perceived by the outer world. More specifically, Life Like Mine aims to bring attention to the ways that racial inequity in the United States has an immediate impact on economic mobility and success in black youth.

shortDescription: An Infinity Blade inspired VR Game
longDescription: We decided to take the classic mobile game "Infinity Blade" and create a VR experience using assets and some gameplay mechanics from the original. Our purpose isn't necessarily to create a VR clone of Infinity Blade, but to use the existing concept to inspire the creation of our own VR universe. This came will be complete with its own story and unique gameplay mechanics in addition to elements from the game it was inspired by. While the entire game won't be complete by the time this project is displayed, the gameplay trailer should give some insight into what our game will include.

shortDescription: Exploring human impact on marine life through a coral reef AR Installation of recycled materials.
longDescription: Humans and their trash problem are poisoning our coral reefs, our oceans, and our earth. I am interested in creating an AR installation that breeds a personal connection with how humans take up space and how it directly affects the environment. I am using the forms of waste that we toss into the trash or recycling for other people to worry about and incorporating it into my work and into the reef models to show how we are fundamentally changing the oceans and our planet beyond recognition.

shortDescription: An instrumental album curated to show my production sound and style.
longDescription: This project is an instrumental album curated to show my sound and production style. Being self-taught in music production, it took me some time to develop my own sound as a producer. I started out copying people I was inspired by, but over time I learned to take the parts of their work that inspired me and add it to my production instead in order to create my own own sound. All songs are produced, arranged, and mixed by me in FL Studio and ProTools. This project is geared to towards music artists.

shortDescription: A line of campus apparel, inspired by yearbook pictures of black and latinx engineers found in the Poly Archives & Special Collections.
longDescription: This project is aligned with the mission of the Black and Latino in STEM committee that seeks to increase the enrollment of Black and Latino men at the NYU Tandon School of Engineering. By transforming archival materials to create clothing that can be leveraged by identity groups on campus, I hope to bring attention to the historic success marginalized groups have had at NYU Tandon and expose the breadth and scope of archival materials that NYU students have open access to. I hope that students can see the finished product as a sort of invitation into the archives, a space that’s there for them to explore and leverage creatively. Ultimately, I'd like for this project to serve as an homage to the black and latinx students of the NYU Tandon School of Engineer, formerly the Brooklyn Polytechnic School of Engineering, I hope that my research and apparel can capture even a modicum of the energy and spirit that these students have bought onto this campus.
usedSoftware: Adobe Photoshop, Adobe Dreamweaver, Scanned "Polywog" Yearbooks (1960-2005) from NYU Poly Archives and Special Collections

shortDescription: A redesign of Instagram's desktop interface.
longDescription: To be able to showcase a fully fleshed out redesign of Instagram's desktop interface. The project focuses mainly on the functionality aspect of Instagram's desktop model, and bettering it. My redesign of Instagram targets areas that would take advantage of the what the desktop environment has to offer. The audience I am targeting is user's of Instagram who would like a seamless experience of the social media platform on their desktop.

shortDescription: An Instagram filter to celebrate NYU 2020 graduation
longDescription: Per Andy Hamilton’s email regarding commencement of Class of 2020 this year, we are not going to have it in person. As a first generation student, I have been looking forward to that moment for a very long time, and My parents cannot attend my commencement as well. So, I now have this idea to use filters to celebrate my graduation and take pride in my school.

shortDescription: A platform that creates things for you to do, when you're unsure what you feel like doing.
longDescription:
Have you ever found yourself unsure what to do? Bored and thinking in circles with no plans and no clue what to do? Then this project is for you.

This concept was originally created to be used in the form of a mobile application, with the ability to suggest hundreds of different activities for you to do based on questions the app asked you and the parameters you set. However, with everything going on in the world and social distancing measures currently in place, I wanted to bring to life a more accessible version of this concept through a website that not only encourages people to stay home, but also provides some relief to those going stir crazy being inside.
usedSoftware: Mobile App: React Native, Figma. Website: Squarespace, HTML/CSS

shortDescription: Mobile app that incentivizes users to keep track of their coding journeys, recording their progress, successes, and struggles
longDescription:
As a black woman who started teaching myself how to code in 2016, the aim of my project was to investigate what black women developers need most, namely those who are self-teaching and live outside of metropolitan areas which hold the majority of educational and professional resources.

Surveys and interviews revealed that black women developers yearned for a supportive community that could serve as a source of motivation in terms of getting started with coding projects and remaining consistent in learning and practicing.

In order to create a communal space for black women to actively take charge of their educational journeys, I organized virtual live-coding sessions meant to facilitate collaboration, development of self-sustaining peer relationships, and augmentation of intrinsic motivation. To coincide with this I designed a mobile app that helps women keep track of how often they're coding and create a personal contact list of people they would like to collaborate/code with in the future.

shortDescription: Bouba/kiki effect on Robots appearance
longDescription: Robots' appearance and interface design strongly influence users' acceptance and functional expectation. Bouba/kiki effect is a non-arbitrary mapping between speech sounds and the visual shape of objects. Based on the theory, I recreate several launched robots with sharp figure and find out if the effect exist on Human-Robot interface design.

shortDescription: Future of music collaboration
longDescription: Repurposing the leap motion controller for use   in live performances and learning music using gestural actions.

shortDescription: It's a series of graphic design with double meaning
longDescription: Everything is comparative in this world just like happiness without sadness has no meaning. I design a series of reversible figures, which means two meaning in one figure, showing the aesthetics of word and contradiction by simple and clean graphic design.

submissionType: Robot class project (using Arduino + muscle wire)
shortDescription: It's alert system robot to tell air pollution in Seoul, Korea.
longDescription: The project is a robot that can measure air pollution in Korea and alert when it exceeds the standard. The petals will consist with muscle wires and will shrink inward to close the flower shape when the air quality exceeds standard limit.

shortDescription: unexpected encounter
longDescription: I’m glad you’re on the other side of this glass screen, clicking and scrolling for means, but in an automated way. Let us defamiliarize our tools and make some reflections.

shortDescription: Test your understanding for prime numbers!
longDescription: The prime number game has 4 difficulty levels with sound effect. In the beginning, users will stay at start page After users click on the button, the game begins. Players have to click the balls with prime number to gain points, however, if you miss the prime ball or click on the wrong one, you'll lose same points on the ball you miss. When score is less than 0, the game is over.

shortDescription: This is a poster that is meant to spread the positive message of blooming through the crumbles.
longDescription: For my Construction of Truth: Special Effects class, our project was to create something with a message on Photoshop (I drew the evil eyes and paint splatter and took a photo of an oil-painted statue and a photo of sunflowers and added some filters) and print it with the risograph. I was inspired by a previous project of mine that focused on helping those with anxiety and similar burnout syndromes. By sending the message to 'bloom through the crumbles' and creating these designs, my goal was to spread positivity. Despite the evil eyes that are on you or if you feel like you're crumbling, you will always bloom.

shortDescription: A transit map of the design industry made to help young designers navigate their early careers.
longDescription: The design industry is broken. We've grown at the cost of creating an infinite tree of titles - most of which either mean the same thing or are misnomers. This is especially a problem for young professionals who are looking to break into the industry or trying to navigate this complex landscape. The transit metaphor serves as friendly way of engaging with the industry. Early designers can better understand what they want to do or transition to. More experienced professionals can contribute and leave feedback, bettering the community.

shortDescription: Autobiography using website as the medium.
longDescription: I chose to make a website focusing on the 4 different cities I lived in that influenced me as a person. I was inspired by work done by other students and professors. I guess it's mainly for myself but also for the NYU community.

shortDescription: A self portrait showing my wild hair.
longDescription: For my photography midterm, I decided to do self portraits. This was one of my favorites of the batch. When I was younger, I used to always straighten my hair and had a mindset that to look beautiful, one had to have straight hair. But as a I grew up, I learned to love my curls and promote self love and acceptance for being natural (or not - I just want everyone to do what they love as long as they're not hurting themselves or others).

shortDescription: A self portrait.
longDescription: For my photography midterm, I decided to do self portraits. This was one of my favorites of the batch. I challenged myself to take more photos of myself since I am always behind the camera. The sun rays that shined through the furniture created these beautiful flower like shapes and I was amazed by the how fresh and abstract they looked on my shoulder.

shortDescription: A Short Cut to understand this human
longDescription: I always wanted to create a space for me to keep all my works and documentation. This is a website I created from scratch, and I wasn’t sure what kind of design I would like to go with, so I began using different colors for different sections. If you take a glance at my work, you will notice that they are all so colorful and energetic. I ended up keeping those bold colors which represent my style vividly. I also incorporated several animal drawings to make the website has a strong feeling of vitality.

shortDescription: A poetry book about homes written in both English and Korean written by Korean Americans.
longDescription:
I am collecting poems from friends to create a poetry book. This book is called 'home.'
A collection of poems, each is a personal home. Written by Korean Americans in English, all poems are also translated in Korean. Both English and Korean poems as well as the designs work all together to portray a beautiful, unique home experience.
usedSoftware: Illustrator, InDesign, iBooks Author, iTunes Producer

shortDescription: A series of Illustrations
longDescription: This is a series of Illustrations for the poem collection by Zhuxue Deren, A Taiwanese poet. In the book, the author plays with the Chinese language and ponders the definition of fiction poems. He often mentions the ocean and rain as a symbol of freedom, or ideal state. So I illustrated several scenes with various forms of water.

shortDescription: Showcasing comfort food, and why that dish has so much value to the individual..
longDescription: I wanted to showcase the similarities and differences of foods that are shared by a lot of people. I wanted to focus on the food and the story dishes can tell, and its impact on people. I was inspired by the movie ratatouille as well as the idea of creating a recipe book. I wanted to create an animated recipe book focusing on food and story-telling. I want people to view foods in different ways and maybe even get inspired to try other people's comfort dishes. As part of the project, I have only created one animated dish, but would like to add on to this book in the future.
usedSoftware: Maya, 3DS Max, Substance Painter, Unreal, Houdini, Projector

shortDescription: We allow users to create their own music from fun sounds of the jungle.
longDescription: Our Jungle Song Maker is a fun way to string together different fun sound effects in the jungle into a song (ex. monkey, birds. rain, coconuts, etc.). As the user clicks on the different sounds, different icons of the sound pop up on the screen and the user has the option to either play with the sounds, add the sounds to a song and play it or both. We came up with the idea because we were excited by the idea of visual and audial stimulation as well as the playful aesthetic of the jungle. Since we are still creating it, we may also add other different variables that the user can play with such as being able to edit pitch.

shortDescription: This JuiceBox just grew a flower in a sudden
longDescription: A grocery keeper started his day by jumping down to the counter. A flower caught his eyes, but what he didn’t know is the magic in his pandora box. The is an animation for my juice box rigging assignment and it’s created with MAYA and rendered with Arnold. In order to make the grocery store has an obsolete and unorganized feeling, I applied a bright blue color shining through the window for the lighting so the entire scene looks more grayish and feels like early morning.

shortDescription: A digital twist of my family's 1930s radio showcasing personal and shared Colombian history and culture.
longDescription: As an immigrant, I noticed how my family dealt with nostalgia throughout our move to the U.S, particularly the ten years in which we couldn't return back home. I wanted to create a website for my family and other Colombian immigrants with the goal of alleviating nostalgia through personal and cultural media. The media is displayed on a digitized version of my family's 1930s radio and consists of a variety of videos, photos, and sounds.
usedSoftware: Proto.Io, Adobe Suite (Premiere Pro, After Effects, Illustrator, Photoshop)

shortDescription: Life goes nonstop
longDescription: Obviously, it’s a looping animation for my walk-cycle assignment. This chicken couldn’t stop herself from walking, even when she dropped her egg. She looks helpless but she decided to continue going and move on without regret. In order to make it feels more creepy and lively, every part of her is moving when she makes a step forward, including eyelids, eyeballs, tongue, tails, wings, etc.
