shortDescription: A speculative multi-sensory exhibition, depicting a symbiotic future habitat in space
longDescription:
My thesis project is inspired by my passion for urban farming, biodesign and space exploration. Biodesign has a unique potential to help us design closed loop regenerative systems in different industries here on Earth; yet, it is still considered a fringe alternative to conventional technologies. Space exploration, however, introduces unprecedented challenges that require radical design and technological solutions. Biodesign could be the integral in developing such solutions.

In this speculative multi-sensory installation, I depict biological technologies used in space exploration habitats of the future. These technologies are designed to create closed loop bioregenerative systems that promote symbiosis among humans and other organisms, while providing the astronauts with essential resources, such as oxygen, food and biomaterial.
usedSoftware: Photoshop, Illustrator, Cinema 4D, After Effects, Adobe Fuse, Webflow, Three.js, etc

shortDescription: Poke or punished
longDescription: Pop The Sound is an interactive VR game for people to get closer to animals. The player is required to identify each sound and pop the corresponding animal. The player will either be confined to a world with many “hangry” animals or peacefully explore around the animal kingdom and get a closer look at each animal. This VR game is made with unreal engine.

shortDescription: A new and accessible way of creating multimodal language for Systems Thinkers in NYC
longDescription: Future Local takes elements of systems design and game design to the world of social media, to create a multimodal, online language toolkit that helps people re-imagine their lives as systems and communities that co-create their futures together.   The game empowers people how to use existing visual vocabularies, like Emojis and Instagram stickers, as well as other features of digital communication, to cross barriers of traditional communication towards a collective consciousness and an idea-driven dialogue.

longDescription: -          With this project I aimed to practice my graphic design skills by designing with a clear goal and objective. I wanted to create something with clean and timeless design, but importantly something that was fun and didn’t take itself too seriously. In this project you will find a logo design, mockups for packaging designs, as well as other brand materials. You can also see my sketches and my process of how I reached the final logo. shortDescription: This is a 3D Animated short about some party going robots who are having a good time doing limbo where the arrogant robot falls to the ground
longDescription: This is a 3D Animated short about some party going robots who are having a good time doing limbo. The video climaxes as the arrogant robot falls to the ground. I worked on this project while in a 3D animation class at NYU using AutoDesk Maya. I made it as a piece for my portfolio and was inspired by real life events but recreated with 3D modeled robots.

shortDescription: A child's desire versus a mother's verdict.
longDescription: This is a final project I made for my 3D Animations class. In this video, a child spots something that they immediately fall in love with at the supermarket. From that moment on, the child does everything in her power to try and convince her mother to bend to her wishes. An emotional and heart wrenching tale of a mother-daughter bond tested by their differences.

shortDescription: this is a 3d animation made by motion capture
longDescription: Motion capture room is an amazing place, you could create so many different thing in there. But the possibilities are limitless only when ones imagination is limitless. I thought it would be interesting if I could create an animation with "superpower". This is something that can not be done easily without motion capture.

shortDescription: Using AR, this project brings awareness to and commemorates the lives of African American women who have died from pregnancy-related causes due to racial biases in the healthcare industry.
longDescription: In the United States, African-American women die from pregnancy-related causes at a rate 3.3 times higher than those of white women. Using augmented reality, the lives of 5 woman, Tashonna Ward, Kira Johnson, Audrey Lockett LaBranche, Lashonda Hazard, and Amber Isaac, are celebrated in a photo gallery display. Upon tapping their respective photos, their unique stories load giving insight to who they were as women and mothers, and the circumstances that led to their death. The goal of this experience is to create awareness of this problem that has worsened for Black women in America and lead to more advocacy for better health care, communication and support.

shortDescription: Motion Capture based 3D animations enhanced in Maya software and staged in Unreal Engine.
longDescription: I conceived the movements, rehearsed and direct the dancers, then captured the motion with Optitrack System. The motion captured was used as a canvas to animate with traditional manual technique in Maya software to add turns, jumps and other advanced dance movements, as well as facial expression. I created and painted the avatars and the world with Substance and composed it in Unreal Engine.

It occurs at the climax of the film, when the main character David gets crushed by a giant being. I made it using the motion capture studio and Maya. It will be used as promotional material as well.

shortDescription: A top-down action rpg game with fast paced combat.
longDescription: Brightblood is a somewhat narrative heavy action RPG with fast paced combat that takes place on an alternate Earth in the future. The main character is the last of her kind; a race with special abilities that can harness and use large amounts of energy. The main character's world is a hostile environment where law enforcement is actively seeking her out and people cannot be easily trusted. She is trying to learn more about her history and her abilities while evading law enforcement. Game play consists of exploring ancient structures as well as a futuristic city. The ancient structures hold knowledge of new abilities, but is where most of the combat takes place. There are also valuable items that can be found and traded for other upgrades.

shortDescription: a better digital experience for intermediate and advanced ESOL learners from East Asian countries to improve their English
longDescription: As an international student, an ESOL (English for Speakers of Other Languages) learner, English has been a big part of my life. Living and studying in the U.S., it matters to me in every aspect of my life, such as academic achievement, job opportunity, friendships, relationships, and even the level of social anxiety and confusion... Most importantly, how well I can represent myself, speak up for myself, and be as confident/comfortable as I can when I am speaking English. Generally, learning English is way more than the scores of the English tests; it's a personal experience, a self-exploration, a lifelong journey. How might we improve the English learning experience digitally?

shortDescription: A story to rekindle the dreamer within us
longDescription: I've always felt like the time I have to do what I love will slowly run out and be replaced by things I have to do. The end of childhood, the end of innocence, the end of naivety. This piece is a tribute to every dreamer, every child that is still alive inside us yearning to dream again. The moon symbolizes the wildness of a child's dream and the raw spirit and curiosity that once ruled our lives.

otherNames: Melissa Canavan, Cailey Ives, Sophia Ferrera
shortDescription: Big Jet Plane is a motion capture performance to the song "Big Jet Plant" by Ahgus&Julia Stone
longDescription: Big Jet Plane is a motion-capture performance to the song "Big Jet Plant" by Angus&Julia Stone. Our story centers around two characters who long to touch each other but are unable to due to circumstances we are unaware of. They long to be with each other, dancing in synchronization and wanting to get away on "a big jet plane". Melissa was in charge of data cleaning, Unreal blueprints, and environment creation, Sophia was in charge of 2D assets and graphics, and Cailey was in charge of cinematography.
usedSoftware: OptiTrack, Motive, Unreal Engine 4.24, Adobe Illustrator, and Premire Pro

shortDescription: Tea Time is a blog that is written for college students looking for inspiration during times of uncertainty.
longDescription: Tea Time with Liw & Val is a blog that discusses health habits and happiness. We communicate with our readers about different ways that we have remained positive during this uncertain time. Additionally, we offer our insights on different events taking place and how we are dealing with them. We hope that readers leave the page feeling inspired, motivated or at least with a smile on their face.

shortDescription: Dream of the Unknown World is a mixed reality project that is created to bring awareness and to encourage others to help motivate sustainability within communities to protect the environment and it's biodiversity.
longDescription: Dream of an Unknown World is a mixed reality project focused on speculative environmental sustainability. Originally inspired by a service trip to Costa Rica on protecting biodiversity, the cancelled trip had inspired me to find a different way to share the speculative thoughts of my friends from the trip. The website is a gallery of the way different individuals view what our planet may become without the continued efforts of environmental health. This project is to encourage and inspire it's audience to understand the results of their actions on our planet Earth.

The goal of the project was to create soundscapes that took inspiration from a singular keyword, which in turn would be an album. I also created an album cover to visually label the project.

shortDescription: The project is a virtual gallery honoring the late, great, Kobe Bryant and his illustrious NBA career.
longDescription: After the tragic accident in January, I felt that I wanted to devote this project to Kobe, who was one of my heroes growing up. He didn't play for my favorite team, but he always gave 110% in everything he did, and I respected him so much for that. The idea was to create a room showcasing his different accolades, achievements, and greatest moments in the NBA.
